        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 5 at 3:04PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 304 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Berea, or 17 miles northwest of Marshall, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fairview, Lassater, Bivins, Pruett, Atlanta, Linden, Berea, Lodi, Red
Hill, Kildare, Queen City, and Jefferson.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
